msgid "General parameters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../metrix.md:48 51e3bd2213ea4f21a19053cd78d18379
msgid ""
"There is a lot of tunable parameters that will be briefly describe "
"inline. Yet the most important one is the `computationType` which "
"determines which kind of computation will be operated:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../metrix.md:50 8916db4656b441a5a63e95b2b0b810d2
msgid ""
"`LF` the LOAD FLOW mode is a basic network flow simulation, production "
"and consumption are fixed and Metrix simulator returns the flow on the "
"lines of the network."
msgstr ""

#: ../../metrix.md:51 f48b5e7a65824c6e9dcf65e6733f8a50
msgid ""
"`OPF_WITHOUT_REDISPATCHING` in this mode, Metrix simulator is allowed to "
"use some actions (topological actions, use of phase tap changers, HVDC "
"lines) to minimize constraints."
msgstr ""

#: ../../metrix.md:52 d3d75d3e245d46e28d3b8ebad47c6838
msgid ""
"`OPF` in OPTIMAL POWER FLOW mode, Metrix simulator will leverage all "
"available actions (that of the previous mode plus generator and load "
"dispatching) to minimize constraints at best cost. If no solution is "
"found, the program will exit with error code 1."
msgstr ""

#: ../../metrix.md:53 567c9b37f2ac418db39436c4636b6fe2
msgid ""
"`OPF_WITH_OVERLOAD` in this OPTIMAL POWER FLOW mode, Metrix simulator "
"works like in the previous mode. If no solution is found, the program "
"returns overload results."
msgstr ""

