#: ../../metrix.md:222 b9c5e0b0cb24410f9df6ac7ad60aba45
msgid "Generators"
msgstr ""

#: ../../metrix.md:224 7a87f5f748684c849f2f1003a0af25fe
msgid "We can define generators whose target can be changed by Metrix:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../metrix.md:225 659e10cb6edf4cc1bb209743227db6ac
msgid "In the adequacy phase to match the production and load"
msgstr ""

#: ../../metrix.md:226 daa65a0a537b4163a43a75dd7b036fbf
msgid ""
"In remedial actions to comply with the defined monitored branch "
"thresholds (only in OPF mode)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../metrix.md:228 dd8ead8c2c254dea992c635d58655979
msgid ""
"For this to happen, we must define ramp up/down costs. Metrix will then "
"adapt the setpoints of the cheapest generators to maintain the "
"generation/demand balance (adequacy phase) or resolve the grid "
"constraints (OPF)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../metrix.md:231 b4b58204043c4009a0bcdcbe8d0b747a
msgid ""
"To solve grid constraints violations in the OPF, there should be at least"
" two generators for Metrix to be able to decrease or increase production "
"in order to respect active power balance. If no generator is configured "
"to be managed by Metrix, then all generators are implicitly managed with "
"zero cost. Note that Metrix will take into account the Pmin and Pmax "
"values of generators (which can be modified through the mapping script). "
"In the same way than most parameters, the value can be a fixed "
"integer/float or a time series name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../metrix.md:236 e589b7b5baa84ff4916a65d364d5269a
msgid ""
"Doctrine costs can be defined for postprocessing purpose (up and down "
"redispatching and costs timeseries)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../metrix.md:238 93fff5f9a538471c82450d750cb12ed0
msgid "The syntax to define a managed generator is:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../metrix.md:252 6b919a4994684eb592f53f739de433e9
msgid ""
"Metrix optimization aims to limit the deviations with respect to the "
"initial production plan, both for adequacy and redispatch. For this "
"reason, Metrix sees all deviations of the initial production plan ($$|P -"
" P0|$$) as a cost. Therefore, both up and down costs (adequacy and "
"redispatch) should be defined as positive costs. The total generation "
"costs for redispatch seen by Metrix is  as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../metrix.md:256 11d4c68187c74cf39b769f8f02026dad
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"\\begin{align*}\n"
"RedispatchCosts = \\sum_{g\\in Generators} RedispatchUp_g \\cdot "
"redispatchUpCosts_g +\n"
"\\sum_{g\\in Generators} RedispatchDown_g \\cdot redispatchDownCosts_g\n"
"\\end{align*}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../metrix.md:263 212ba15a199840cb9d00bed0218e28ac
msgid "With"
msgstr ""

#: ../../metrix.md:265 5892ba382a6a43ed8c1431510f9a06f6
msgid "$RedispatchUp_g = max(P_g - P0_g, 0)$,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../metrix.md:267 828e155095ea46fb95e16100eab5c6ae
msgid "$RedispatchDown_g = max(P0_g - P_g, 0)$."
msgstr ""

#: ../../metrix.md:269 a1805c5b82324ff395887b09db1add6a
msgid ""
"It should be noted that this is different from redispatching cost in real"
" systems' operation, where in case of downwards activations, the "
"generator _pays_ the TSO for the generation reduction (not delivered "
"energy). Moreover, to prioritize topological solutions over redispatch "
"solutions, the redispatching up and down costs have a lower bound of >= "
"0.5. Metrix will correct any adequacy or redispatch cost below the lower "
"bound, setting it to lower bound value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../metrix.md:272 cc9ba8424b624a7bb950e3ba57ba79a8
msgid ""
"Note that if at least one generator is managed, then only defined "
"generators will be managed to match adequacy. In some cases, it could "
"result in a program failure (return code -1) where constraints cannot be "
"resolved in OPF mode. Also:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../metrix.md:273 5617871c42a64123b326e6c190dcd20c
msgid ""
"Generators used for the adequacy phase are not necessarily the same used "
"for the redispatching phase. If `onContingency` isn't defined but "
"`redispatchingCost` is, then the generator will be used only in "
"preventive actions. For the generator to be fully used for preventive and"
" curative remedial action, both of these parameters must be defined."
msgstr ""

#: ../../metrix.md:274 1c00b37d8f9640ecb2ebc60d2cf35450
msgid ""
"Cost must always be defined for both directions. If we want to prevent a "
"generator to ramp up or down, we can set a high prohibitive cost."
msgstr ""

#: ../../metrix.md:275 ba461e27da994d55ba9fca54570c9556
msgid "Rules that take into account Pmax and Pmin are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../metrix.md:276 516ff587a2bb4412900cd294d78eb142
msgid ""
"if the targetP is out of bounds (targetP > Pmax or targetP < Pmin) then "
"targetP is adjusted to the closest bound. This can happen when `ignore-"
"limits` is set in the mapping script or the tool parameter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../metrix.md:277 622583f354e941f6898fba2458a1f109
msgid ""
"during the adequacy phase, the Pmax constraints are enforced but Pmin are"
" temporary set to 0. It results that a (only one at most) generator can "
"have a targetP out of its lower bound (0 < targetP < Pmin)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../metrix.md:278 6c7efbe543af48bfa1d471ae465d567a
msgid ""
"in the redispatching phase, generators with Pmin < targetP < Pmax are "
"enforced between their bounds. If a group have an initial targetP below "
"Pmin, the constraints will be initialTargetP < targetP < Pmax."
msgstr ""

